    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small, narrow, usually three-pronged forks made with short tines and a long handle, intended for eating appetizers or small pieces of seafood or oysters; often resembling a trident.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
